class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://github.com/features/copilot\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Learn More</a>\n                            | 2026-02-18\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <span class=\"product-name\">Windsurf</span>\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://codeium.com/windsurf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Wave 13 Release with SWE-1.5 Model\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            Windsurf released Wave 13, introducing the SWE-1.5 'Penguin Alpha' model as default with free 3-month access. Features include context window indicator, multi-session parallel view, Cascade Hooks for lifecycle actions, and Git Worktrees support.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type release\">Release</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://codeium.com/windsurf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Release Notes</a>\n                            | 2026-02-17\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"community-feedback\">\n                            <div class=\"feedback-item\">\"Free for all developers for 3 months - significant accessibility improvement\" <span class=\"feedback-source\">— Developer community <span class=\"sentiment-positive\">↑</span></span></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <span class=\"product-name\">Claude Code</span>\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://claude.ai/code\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Claude Sonnet 4.6 Release with Enhanced Code Processing\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            Anthropic released Claude Sonnet 4.6 featuring enhanced code processing, accelerated long-text reasoning, and becoming the new default model. Achieved 79.6% on SWE-bench Verified and 72.5% on OSWorld-Verified.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type release\">Release</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://claude.ai/code\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Learn More</a>\n                            | 2026-02-17\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"community-feedback\">\n                            <div class=\"feedback-item\">\"Claude Code now contributes 4% of GitHub public commits, projected to exceed 20% by end of 2026\" <span class=\"feedback-source\">— Industry analytics <span class=\"sentiment-positive\">↑</span></span></div>\n                            <div class=\"feedback-item\">\"Completes tasks in 30 seconds vs GPT-5.2 taking 7 minutes\" <span class=\"feedback-source\">— Reddit comparisons <span class=\"sentiment-positive\">↑</span></span></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <span class=\"product-name\">Claude Code</span>\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.50\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Version 2.1.50 - Major Bug Fixes\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            Added support for startupTimeout configuration for LSP servers, WorktreeCreate and WorktreeRemove hook events. Fixed critical bugs: resumed sessions visibility with symlinks, session data loss on SSH disconnect, and memory leaks.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type release\">Release</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.50\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Release Notes</a>\n                            | 2026-02-20\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <span class=\"product-name\">Claude Code</span>\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/building-c-compiler\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Building a C Compiler with Agent Teams\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            Anthropic engineer Nicholas Carlini developed 'agent teams' - multiple Claude Code instances working in parallel on a shared codebase. Over 2,000 sessions and $20,000 in API costs, 16 agents produced a 100,000-line Rust-based C compiler.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type announcement\">Announcement</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/building-c-compiler\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Read More</a>\n                            | 2026-02-16\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <span class=\"product-name\">Devin</span>\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://devin.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Cognition Reaches $10.2B Valuation\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            Cognition.AI reached a $10.2 billion valuation, making it the highest-valued company in the AI programming sector after raising over $400 million in funding. ARR grew from $1M (September 2024) to $73M (June 2025).\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type announcement\">Announcement</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://devin.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Learn More</a>\n                            | 2026-02-09\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <span class=\"product-name\">Windsurf</span>\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://codeium.com/windsurf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Cognition Acquisition Impact\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            February 2026 reports highlight Cognition's acquisition of Windsurf (July 2025): combined ARR doubled with 30%+ post-merger growth, reaching $10.2 billion valuation. Integration created full-stack platform combining Devin's autonomous AI engineer with Windsurf's AI IDE.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type announcement\">Announcement</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://codeium.com/windsurf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Learn More</a>\n                            | 2026-02-15\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <span class=\"product-name\">GitHub Copilot</span>\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://github.com/features/copilot\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Claude Sonnet 4.6 Integration\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            GitHub Copilot integrated Anthropic's Claude Sonnet 4.6 model, excelling at complex agentic coding tasks and search operations. Available across VS Code, Visual Studio, web, mobile, and CLI.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://github.com/features/copilot\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Learn More</a>\n                            | 2026-02-15\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"community-feedback\">\n                            <div class=\"feedback-item\">\"Users preferred Sonnet 4.6 over Sonnet 4.5 in 70% of cases. 59% preferred Sonnet 4.6 over Opus 4.5\" <span class=\"feedback-source\">— Anthropic Testing <span class=\"sentiment-positive\">↑</span></span></div>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <span class=\"product-name\">Codex CLI</span>\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                GPT-5.3-Codex Model Release\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            OpenAI released GPT-5.3-Codex in February 2026, featuring 25% faster performance than GPT-5.2-Codex with 69-72% score on SWE-bench Verified. Also released macOS application and GPT-5.3-Spark ultra-fast version.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type release\">Release</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://developers.openai.com/codex/changelog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Changelog</a>\n                            | 2026-02-12\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                </div>\n            </section>\n\n            <!-- Technical Insights Section -->\n            <section class=\"column technical-insights\">\n                <div class=\"column-header\">Technical Insights</div>\n                <div class=\"column-content\">\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.63\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Claude Code v2.1.63: Multiple slash commands and memory improvements\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            Anthropic released Claude Code v2.1.63 with /simplify and /batch bundled slash commands, HTTP hooks for external integrations, and extensive memory leak fixes across the platform (20+ fixes). This update focuses on improving developer workflow integration and system stability.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.63\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Read More</a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"topics\">\n                            <span class=\"topic\">AI coding</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">developer tools</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">Claude Code</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">memory management</span>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://github.com/continuedev/continue/releases\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Continue v1.3.32: MCP App support and cn checks\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            Continue released v1.3.32 adding limited MCP App support, cn checks CLI command, enabled agent mode for LM Studio models, updated default model to Claude Opus 4.6, and consolidated React best practices. This release continues expanding MCP ecosystem integration.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://github.com/continuedev/continue/releases\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Read More</a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"topics\">\n                            <span class=\"topic\">AI coding</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">MCP</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">Continue</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">agent mode</span>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://cursor.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Cursor Bugbot Autofix with Cloud Agents\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            Cursor's Bugbot can automatically fix issues it finds in pull requests using cloud agents that run in isolated VMs with full development environments. Over 35% of autofix changes are merged into base PRs. Resolution rate increased from 52% to 76%. Community feedback highlights efficiency gains but also concerns about over-reliance and code understanding.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://cursor.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Read More</a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"topics\">\n                            <span class=\"topic\">AI coding</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">Cursor</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">autonomous agents</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">PR automation</span>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://cursor.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Cursor Cloud Agents with Computer Use\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            Cursor released Cloud Agents with computer use capabilities - agents can now use the software they create to test changes and demo their work, producing merge-ready PRs with artifacts (videos, screenshots, and logs). Available on web, desktop, mobile, Slack, and GitHub. This represents a significant advancement in agentic capabilities.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://cursor.com/changelog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Read More</a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"topics\">\n                            <span class=\"topic\">AI coding</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">Cursor</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">computer use</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">autonomous agents</span>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"item\">\n                        <div class=\"item-title\">\n                            <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.59\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                                Claude Code v2.1.59: Auto-memory and /copy command\n                            </a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-description\">\n                            Claude Code v2.1.59 introduced auto-memory where Claude automatically saves useful context to auto-memory with /memory management, plus /copy command with interactive picker for code blocks. Community feedback was mixed: positive for solving cross-session memory pain points, but negative for performance issues and unwanted memory writing behavior.\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"item-meta\">\n                            <span class=\"update-type feature\">Feature</span>\n                            <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.59\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Read More</a>\n                        </div>\n                        <div class=\"topics\">\n                            <span class=\"topic\">AI coding</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">Claude Code</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">memory management</span>\n                            <span class=\"topic\">context management</span>\n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n\n                </div>\n            </section>\n        </main>\n\n        <footer>\n            <a href=\"#\">Archive</a>\n            <a href=\"#\">About</a>\n            <a href=\"#\">RSS Feed</a>\n            <a href=\"#\">GitHub</a>\n            <p style=\"margin-top: 10px; font-size: 8pt;\">Generated with Claude Code • Data updated daily</p>\n        </footer>\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>"
